qas.question: In the 2001 general election, The Times declared support for what political party?
What is the name of the political party's leader that The Times supported in the 2001 general election?
For the 2010 general election, which political party did The Times support?
What political party did the Tories have to form a coalition with in 2010?
What political party was re-elected by a landslide in 2001?

context: For the 2001 general election The Times declared its support for <a1_0>Tony Blair<a1_0/>'s <a0_0><a4_0>Labour<a4_0/><a0_0/> government, which was re-elected by a landslide. It supported Labour again in 2005, when Labour achieved a third successive win, though with a reduced majority. For the 2010 general election, however, the newspaper declared its support for the Tories once again; the election ended in the <a2_0>Tories<a2_0/> taking the most votes and seats but having to form a coalition with the <a3_0>Liberal Democrats<a3_0/> in order to form a government as they had failed to gain an overall majority.
